file=Brand Studio/muse/operational/commands/muse-commands.md · h=name: muse-commands\ntype: operational/commands\nstatus: consolidated from trigger phrases in muse's skill files — no new triggers invented\nassigned_agent: muse (Brand Studio / Ideation)\ndate_added: 2026-07-07\n · p:=Routing reference for muse.\n · tb=\| Skill \| Natural-language triggers \| Shortcut \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| generate-creative-ideas \| "campaign ideas," "brainstorm this," "I'm stuck," "give me concepts," "content ideas" \| `/muse-ideate` \| · tb=\| concept-library \| "have we done this before," "what's in the reserve," "log this concept," "why was X rejected" \| `/muse-library` \| · tb=\| (full pipeline) \| any ideation brief — generation always closes with the library phase \| `/muse-run` \| · ### Generation always closes with the library=No run ends at a raw idea list: dedupe → score → top-3-to-spark → register is the mandatory tail.\n · ### Divergent before convergent, always=Never score while generating (the source's rule 1); pushes past first-round outputs before any NAF pass.\n · ### What muse does NOT take=- Developing the creative → lena/pixel/pulse per format.\n- Narrative positioning → weave. Final review/gate → spark.\n- Growth experiment ideas → muse generates; nate's ICE backlog owns them after.\n · f:=Unclear ask → the source skill's context questions ("what problem? what have you tried?") before any technique fires.\n